Numbering Systems
- Hexadecimal numbers 
  + (0-9) (10-15)
- Binary Numbers
- Base 16 
- Converting Dotted Decimal to Binary Numbers
- Converting Binary Numbers to Dotted Decimal 
- Open Systems Interconnection Model (OSI)
  + 7 application | 6 Presentation | 5 Session | 4 Transport | 3 Network | 2 Data-Link | 1 Physical 
  + Data-Link (MAC , Frame) Rule: Token ; Chaos Theory = Ethernet ; Network Card; Bridge (Wired)/ Access Point (Wireless)
  + Rules for each layer - Media Access Control (M.A.C)(order of first, Token, Coax, Type of Attenna)
  + Host Layer and Media Layers
    *Host Layer (Bits, Frames, Packets) Media Layers (Segments, Data, Data, Data)
    *"Chaos theory" - Probability and Ethernet
    APPLICATION LAYER - Network process to application  // Data
    PRESENTATION - Data Representation and Encryption  // Data
    SESSION - Interhost Communication // Data
    TRANSPORT - Path Determination and IP (Logical Addressing) // Segment
    DATA LINK - MAC and LLC (Physical Addressing) // Frames - Physical Address MAC address
    PHYSICAL - media, signal, and binary transmission // Bits
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Bridges - always have two switches. Switches - has many port changes.
    
